    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>National Taiwan University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to understand whether generic ceftazidime causes different
      adverse drug reaction incidence from the brand drug.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Ceftazidime is a third generation cephalosporins that should be reserved for severe bacterial
      infections. Substitution of the brand ceftazidime with a generic ceftazidime raised some
      concerns.

      The purpose of this study is to understand whether generic ceftazidime causes different
      adverse drug reaction incidence from the brand drug.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
